<br>
Your math is wrong.<br>
<br>
Big Guild Mob 1 = 2 loots<br>
Big Guild Mob 2 = 2 loots<br>
Small guild A, small guild B = 1 loot each<br>
Small guild A mob 2 = 2 loots<br>
Small guild B mob 2 = 2 loots<br>
<br>
Summary<br>
Big Guild = 4 loots<br>
Small Guild A = 3 loots, one of which they would never have seen alone.<br>
Small Guild B = 3 loots, one of which they would never have seen alone.<br>
Total Small Guild A/B ad hoc convenience alliance = 6 loots<br>
<br>
Now do you understand?<br>
