<br>
Put AD/Grummus/Behemoth on rotation     <br>
<br>
Guilds may quickly lose interest in doing these mobs for many reasons.  It could be that they have exausted the loot table from these mobs, or that the effort to kill is not commensurate with the reward.  We have seen now that the larger guilds capable of killing AD are not that interested in this mob, most likely because they are VT capable and this presents a better avenue to equiping their guild (time vs reward).  As more guilds start being interested in these mobs, especially those guilds who are not in VT/Ssha, we may one day see this mob as being contested and hence the rotation system will be neccessary to ensure order and fairness on the rathe.  <br>
<br>
As I understand it, AD was up for three days before CB/VoLS killed him.  That is a far cry from a mob being in any way contested, but as I explained above, this lack of interest in the mob may not last.  <br>
<br>
Seeing as this mob does present an obstacle to progress through the content in PoP, I propose that there should be an option to gather up sufficient force to take down these mobs without incuring any penalty from other rotations.  <br>
<br>
My suggestion:<br>
<br>
When a guild passes on their turn to kill these flag mobs, there should be a grace period to allow others not on the rotation to attempt the mob.  If the attempt is from a single guild then a success would qualify them a spot on the rotation.  If another avenue was taken to overcome AD/Grummus/Behemoth, then a new rotation entry is not created and members of the raid only leave with the flags and the loot they earned.  <br>
<br>
Note: Grace period suggestion:<br>
              this can be as simple as informing guild up for rotation that you have an interest in attempting the mob should the guild choose to pass.  When that is the case, the guild defers the kill to the person who requested instead of the guild next on the rotation.<br>
<br>
In this scheme, the rotation on mobs that are weakly contested (as shown by the pass) are relaxed allowing different avenues of progression through PoP (teaming/pick up raid).   Also note that a guild wishing to get on the rotation should not need to wait for a pass, but instead follow the normal procedure.<br>
<br>
Of course this is just a suggestion <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Sprigg Skittlebrow<br>
60 Rogue<br>
