I don't think you're examples disproved my argument.  Let's use your claim:<br>
<br>
Teaming up is unfair.<br>
Make a contradictory statement: Teaming up is fair.<br>
There are no rules against teaming up on non rotation mobs.<br>
All guilds have the ability to team up on non rotation mobs without breaking any rules.<br>
Definition of Unfairness: Not just or evenhanded; biased.<br>
Negation of Unfairness (fairness): just or evenhanded; unbiased.<br>
Since all guilds have the same opertunity to team up, it is unbiased.<br>
Since teaming up is unbiased, by definition, it is fair.<br>
Since teaming up is fair, it can not be the case that teaming up is unfair.<br>
