There are 3 things that make you able to successfully able to kill a mob in EQ.  <br>
1.)  The tactics to kill the mob.  Some mobs are very simple, while others require more complicate tactics.<br>
2.)  Enough people to perform those tactics.  If you are using a CH rotation, you need enough clerics in the rotation to heal the MT fast enough to offset the damage dealy to them.<br>
3.)  Powerful enough characters (in terms of both levels and gear) to perform thier duty in an adequate fashion to enable you to kill the mob.  Your clerics need enough mana, your tanks need enough hit points, your wizards need thier spells, etc etc<br>
<br>
Just because I disagree with you that all it takes to beat an encounter is more people, does not mean I don't realise that some enounter do require more people.<br>
