Plllleeeeeaasssseee, get a grip people.<br>
<br>
Can't say I've read every single post.  If I had, I would currently be undergoing therapy of some description to stop the voices in my head... but I've certainly read enough to  think I can summarise this fairly simply.<br>
<br>
1.  An incident occured involving teaming on a non-rot mob. Although not against the rules, it brought to light some concerns from certain guilds.<br>
<br>
2.  Questions are now being asked regarding the non-rot status of the mob and whether or not it should be looked at for the future.<br>
<br>
           a/ Suggestion has been made that the mob be put on the rot cycle to avoid future teaming efforts.<br>
           b/ countering the suggestion listed as a/ is the fact that there is a quest that results in the same flagging as the kill, thereby negating the need for rotational status<br>
<br>
That's it, in a nutshell, once you wade through all the accusations and name calling and stuff better suited to the flame section. And once you get past the &quot;some rots are outdated&quot; etc etc (which I personally feel is valid but should not cloud this discussion).<br>
<br>
Might I respectfully ask that the powers that be comment on the above points (and not lapse into he said, she said banter)...<br>
<br>
